column5: Nice Simon, you kicked your buddies butt out there.  Variety is a good thing, but if I lived up your way I wouldn't bother with the lakers, it would be walleye, walleye and more walleye.

Nice Simon, you kicked your buddies butt out there.  Variety is a good thing, but if I lived up your way I wouldn't bother with the lakers, it would be walleye, walleye and more walleye.   I here ya Chris, in the summer I tend to be a walleye fisherman 90% of the time with 5% crappie and 5% lakers, but in the winter I find almost all my walleye fishing a bit tedious, whitefish and trout provide the adrenaline rush I need!
